Here's everything you need to know, broken down simply:

What does the Anthropic API key do?

It's what powers the AI brain inside VidLaunch. When you click "Generate," your app sends your video topic to Claude (Anthropic's AI) which writes all the platform-optimized titles, descriptions, and hashtags. The API key is basically your login pass that authorizes those requests. Without it, the app has no AI — it can't generate anything.

Do you need to pay?

Anthropic gives new accounts $5 in free API credits to start — no credit card needed for the initial credits. That's enough to test the app quite a few times. 
Price Per Token

After that, yes it's pay-as-you-go. The model VidLaunch uses (Claude Sonnet 4.6) costs $3 per million input tokens and $15 per million output tokens. 
metacto

In plain terms for your use case: Each time you hit "Generate" in VidLaunch, it uses roughly 1,000–2,000 tokens total. That works out to about $0.01–$0.03 per generation — less than a penny or two per use. Your $5 in free credits would cover 200–500 generations before you'd need to add a card.

Does it have limits?

Yes — new accounts start at lower rate limits (requests per minute, tokens per minute) and can request increases as usage grows. For personal use generating social media content, you'll never come close to hitting those limits. 
Finout

Bottom line for you: Start with the free $5 credits at console.anthropic.com — sign up, grab your key, and you're good to go. At a penny or two per video optimization, it's extremely affordable even when you do need to top up.

